<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-01-18T06:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-01-18T06:00:00-05:00" n="271" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d271">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 893.811/241</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Reinsch</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Peking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-01-18T19:00:00+08:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">January 18, 1917, 7
                                p.m</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>With reference to my telegram of January 11, 6 p.m. Representatives of
                            International Corporation found Chinese authorities unwilling to
                            entertain proposal but they hope that Chinese authorities will agree to
                            the issue of part of the bonds at Tokyo. The American corporation could
                            do the negotiations alone, retaining the entire management. Carey has
                            informed Japanese Legation who say they will report favorably to
                            Tokyo.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Reinsch</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>